I = 2\int_0^\infty\ e^{-x^{2\infty}} = 2\,\left(\,\int_0^1\ e^{-x^\infty} + \int_1^\infty\ e^{-x^\infty}\right) = 2\,\left(\,\int_0^1\ e^{-0} + \int_1^\infty\ e^{-\infty}\right)
\quad\qquad = 2\,\left(\,\int_0^1 1\ dx + \int_1^\infty 0\ dx\right)\quad = 2\,(1\cdot1 + 0) = 2
